## Essential Tools 🛠️
•	npm (Node Package Manager):
o	What it is: The world's largest software registry and the command-line tool used to manage project dependencies.
o	Its Role in EventRush: It was our toolbox. We used it to install all our backend packages like Express, Mongoose, and bcrypt.
•	dotenv:
o	What it is: A package that loads environment variables from a .env file into process.env.
o	Its Role in EventRush: It was our secret keeper. It allowed us to store sensitive information like our database connection string and JWT secret in a separate .env file, keeping it out of our main codebase for better security.
•	bcrypt.js:
o	What it is: A library for hashing passwords.
o	Its Role in EventRush: It was our password scrambler. We never store passwords in plain text. When a user registers, bcrypt takes their password and turns it into a long, irreversible string (a hash). When they log in, it compares the hash of the entered password with the one in the database.
•	JWT (JSON Web Tokens):
o	What it is: A standard for securely transmitting information between parties as a JSON object.
o	Its Role in EventRush: It's the user's ID card or hall pass. After a user logs in, the server gives them a JWT. For every protected action (like participating in an event), the user shows this token to the server. The server verifies it to confirm who they are without needing to ask for a password again.
•	MongoDB Atlas:
o	What it is: MongoDB's official cloud database service.
o	Its Role in EventRush: Instead of installing and managing a database on our own computer, we used Atlas. It's a Database-as-a-Service that handled all the hosting, security, and maintenance for us, which is much easier for development.
